WEBVTT

1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:04,004
[♪ gentle music playing]

2
00:00:16,683 --> 00:00:18,685
[gate buzzer blares]

3
00:00:26,276 --> 00:00:28,945
Mr. Manigan,
I'm sure you are well aware

4
00:00:29,029 --> 00:00:30,864
{\an8}this is your last shot.

5
00:00:30,947 --> 00:00:32,699
{\an8}You're a two-time offender.

6
00:00:33,908 --> 00:00:36,036
{\an8}Why should anyone believe
anything you say at this point?

7
00:00:37,787 --> 00:00:39,581
[board member 1] Would you take
the durag off, please?

8
00:00:39,664 --> 00:00:40,665
Yes, ma'am.

9
00:00:44,627 --> 00:00:46,588
I've done the work on myself,

10
00:00:46,671 --> 00:00:49,674
and I know I'm, uh,
I'm still a-- a work in progress.

11
00:00:49,758 --> 00:00:52,594
[board member 3] Please tell us,
what are your plans for your life?

12
00:00:52,677 --> 00:00:56,723
More importantly, are you able to express
genuine contrition?

13
00:00:58,850 --> 00:01:00,894
[board member 2] Mr. Manigan,
do you know what contrition is?

14
00:01:02,937 --> 00:01:04,898
It's being sorry for what I've done.

15
00:01:06,024 --> 00:01:07,025
And I am.

16
00:01:09,569 --> 00:01:10,570
Very sorry.

17
00:01:16,826 --> 00:01:19,162
I buried my eldest son
during my time in here.

18
00:01:21,706 --> 00:01:24,084
And I'd like to get home
to my youngest

19
00:01:24,167 --> 00:01:26,503
so the same thing
don't happen to him.

20
00:01:28,004 --> 00:01:29,631
I need to get back to Southeast.

21
00:01:30,632 --> 00:01:32,092
At least try to do some good.

22
00:01:36,304 --> 00:01:39,224
Not a day go by that I don't feel
an overwhelming sense of guilt.

23
00:01:40,892 --> 00:01:42,143
I'm damaged, I know that.

24
00:01:44,729 --> 00:01:45,980
But I'm still useful.

25
00:01:47,148 --> 00:01:48,775
[board member 2]
What about boxing?

26
00:01:49,692 --> 00:01:52,153
I'm sure there's a lot
that you have left to offer.

27
00:01:53,780 --> 00:01:54,989
I don't know.

28
00:01:55,782 --> 00:01:57,700
To be honest, I lost the love for it.

29
00:01:59,869 --> 00:02:01,496
Haunts me more than anything.

30
00:02:03,832 --> 00:02:05,291
[loud student chatter]

31
00:02:05,375 --> 00:02:08,586
[over intercom]<i> Attention, students,</i>
<i>don't forget to sign up in your homeroom</i>

32
00:02:08,670 --> 00:02:10,338
<i>for the Fall Festival Talent Show.</i>

33
00:02:10,839 --> 00:02:13,007
<i>Don't miss your chance to win</i>
<i>lots of fun prizes.</i>

34
00:02:13,091 --> 00:02:14,259
-[♪ Twin rapping]
-[♪ Quincey beatboxing]

35
00:02:14,342 --> 00:02:15,343
<i>♪ It's not a problem, it's a fact ♪</i>

36
00:02:15,426 --> 00:02:17,053
<i>♪ Three plus zero,</i>
<i>no joke no need to react ♪</i>

37
00:02:17,137 --> 00:02:18,471
<i>♪ I see you tryna act tough ♪</i>

38
00:02:18,555 --> 00:02:20,181
<i>♪ Everything a sham</i>
<i>everything is a bluff ♪</i>

39
00:02:20,265 --> 00:02:21,516
<i>♪ I get it you just wanna be like me ♪</i>

40
00:02:21,599 --> 00:02:23,351
<i>♪ But the only problem is</i>
<i>your IQ is three ♪</i>

41
00:02:24,310 --> 00:02:25,436
[crowd exclaiming]

42
00:02:25,520 --> 00:02:26,563
Yo, man.

43
00:02:26,646 --> 00:02:28,648
[loud student chatter continues]

44
00:02:33,695 --> 00:02:35,530
[school bell ringing]

45
00:02:35,613 --> 00:02:38,616
[♪ bright uplifting music playing]

46
00:02:47,208 --> 00:02:50,211
[♪ bright uplifting music
continues playing]

47
00:03:39,636 --> 00:03:41,346
[drawer clattering]

48
00:03:42,931 --> 00:03:44,682
[keys jingling]

49
00:03:44,766 --> 00:03:48,228
[♪ bright uplifting music
continues playing]

50
00:03:48,311 --> 00:03:50,271
[friends chattering indistinctly]

51
00:03:50,355 --> 00:03:51,940
I'll do it. Which key?

52
00:03:54,108 --> 00:03:55,401
[both chatting excitedly]

53
00:03:56,236 --> 00:03:57,904
Dang, whoa!

54
00:03:58,988 --> 00:03:59,989
Dang!

55
00:04:10,792 --> 00:04:12,293
Hey, get up here! Get up here!

56
00:04:20,760 --> 00:04:22,762
[both grunting]

57
00:04:25,682 --> 00:04:27,600
[both groaning playfully]

58
00:04:27,684 --> 00:04:29,686
[distant siren wailing]

59
00:04:31,646 --> 00:04:33,022
[door opens]

60
00:04:34,482 --> 00:04:35,775
[door closes]

61
00:04:39,320 --> 00:04:40,905
I wanna have this conversation
with you, I do, I just--

62
00:04:40,989 --> 00:04:42,532
I can't right now, I got a lot...

63
00:04:42,615 --> 00:04:44,701
-I got-- I got stuff to do.
-Ketta. Ketta, stop.

64
00:04:44,784 --> 00:04:46,077
-Stop, please.
-No, I...

65
00:04:46,869 --> 00:04:47,870
I'll stop.

66
00:04:49,205 --> 00:04:50,373
Well, now you gotta start.

67
00:04:52,083 --> 00:04:53,084
Um...

68
00:04:59,382 --> 00:05:00,883
I wanna see my son.

69
00:05:02,093 --> 00:05:03,845
That's what you want?

70
00:05:03,928 --> 00:05:05,471
[Walt] That's not what I'm saying.
I mean, I...

71
00:05:07,473 --> 00:05:09,100
Come on, Ketta.
I'm-- I'm not the enemy.

72
00:05:09,183 --> 00:05:11,060
[Ketta] Walt, you don't get
to just re-insert yourself.

73
00:05:11,144 --> 00:05:12,812
I know.

74
00:05:12,895 --> 00:05:13,896
I know, I know.

75
00:05:15,106 --> 00:05:17,108
You gotta put in the work.

76
00:05:17,191 --> 00:05:18,276
You gotta...

77
00:05:19,360 --> 00:05:22,030
let go of that part of yourself
that only know how to destroy.

78
00:05:24,073 --> 00:05:25,783
Come on, baby,
don't-- don't say that.

79
00:05:28,119 --> 00:05:29,287
I thought-- I thought-- I thought--

80
00:05:29,370 --> 00:05:30,747
I thought you was past all that.

81
00:05:33,207 --> 00:05:34,292
[Ketta] Are you?

82
00:05:37,837 --> 00:05:39,255
You got some place to stay?

83
00:05:40,423 --> 00:05:42,633
-[Walt] I wanna come home.
-No, I'm not-- I'm not--

84
00:05:42,717 --> 00:05:44,344
I'm not saying
you can stay here, I'm just--

85
00:05:44,427 --> 00:05:45,428
Please.

86
00:05:46,304 --> 00:05:47,430
Can I come home?

87
00:05:48,765 --> 00:05:50,683
Walt, you gotta do the work first.

88
00:05:53,186 --> 00:05:54,187
Okay?

89
00:05:56,814 --> 00:05:58,024
Wait, wait, Ketta.

90
00:05:59,025 --> 00:06:00,026
Ketta.

91
00:06:02,236 --> 00:06:03,321
I love you.

92
00:06:05,531 --> 00:06:06,908
I know you do.

93
00:06:09,285 --> 00:06:10,286
Ketta.

94
00:06:11,996 --> 00:06:12,997
Ketta, hold up.

95
00:06:21,381 --> 00:06:23,383
[car starting]

96
00:06:33,434 --> 00:06:36,396
[♪ gentle music playing]

97
00:06:42,193 --> 00:06:44,195
[students chattering]

98
00:06:44,570 --> 00:06:46,197
[Slim]
<i>...gotta get our legs strong enough.</i>

99
00:06:46,280 --> 00:06:48,908
So, one more time, we're gonna do
a one-minute drill on the kicks.

100
00:06:48,991 --> 00:06:51,452
Kick from your hip, and go!

101
00:06:51,536 --> 00:06:53,538
Make sure-- get a splash,
I wanna see a splash!

102
00:06:53,621 --> 00:06:55,623
-That's it.
-[water splashing]

103
00:06:57,750 --> 00:06:58,751
Keep going.

104
00:07:00,169 --> 00:07:01,170
Keep going.

105
00:07:05,466 --> 00:07:07,009
Keep going, make sure you kick.

106
00:07:11,556 --> 00:07:12,849
That's it, good job.

107
00:07:14,684 --> 00:07:16,686
[people chattering]

108
00:07:20,648 --> 00:07:22,650
[video game playing]

109
00:07:32,702 --> 00:07:33,911
[person coughing]

110
00:07:41,836 --> 00:07:43,838
[computer keys clacking]

111
00:07:47,508 --> 00:07:48,551
Bruh, you good?

112
00:07:50,094 --> 00:07:51,721
Uh, not really.

113
00:07:56,142 --> 00:07:58,144
[computer keys clacking]

114
00:08:00,146 --> 00:08:01,481
-[computer dings]
-Got it.

115
00:08:04,025 --> 00:08:05,610
-Thanks, man.
-You're welcome.

116
00:08:10,531 --> 00:08:12,200
[quietly muttering]

117
00:08:12,783 --> 00:08:14,785
[children shouting outside]

118
00:08:18,623 --> 00:08:20,124
-Get off me, man!
-[loud thwack]

119
00:08:21,918 --> 00:08:23,920
-[♪ intense music playing]
-[kid] Don't take my shoes, please!

120
00:08:24,003 --> 00:08:25,129
-Please!
-[Walt] Hey!

121
00:08:26,172 --> 00:08:27,924
[kid groaning]

122
00:08:32,345 --> 00:08:33,679
Hey, little man, you alright?

123
00:08:35,723 --> 00:08:37,016
Come on, get up.

124
00:08:40,978 --> 00:08:43,981
Hey, even if you lose, man,
you gotta fight back.

125
00:08:44,065 --> 00:08:45,149
You hear me?

126
00:08:46,484 --> 00:08:47,485
Come on.

127
00:08:52,949 --> 00:08:54,367
You'll be alright.

128
00:08:57,495 --> 00:08:58,871
Hey!

129
00:08:58,955 --> 00:09:01,165
Uh-uh. Get him outta here.

130
00:09:02,458 --> 00:09:05,002
Hey, come on, bruh.
He need some love.

131
00:09:05,086 --> 00:09:06,587
Peroxide and some Band-Aids.

132
00:09:06,671 --> 00:09:07,880
All the youngs know,

133
00:09:07,964 --> 00:09:09,590
you fight out there,
you don't fight in here.

134
00:09:09,674 --> 00:09:11,467
He wasn't fighting, they jumped him.

135
00:09:12,718 --> 00:09:14,595
The kid don't even know
how to defend himself, man.

136
00:09:14,679 --> 00:09:16,347
I saw the whole thing
from the computer lab.

137
00:09:16,430 --> 00:09:17,765
The computer lab? Who are you?

138
00:09:17,848 --> 00:09:19,016
I'm Walt.

139
00:09:19,100 --> 00:09:21,102
[kids grunting playfully]

140
00:09:21,185 --> 00:09:23,020
-Hyah!
-[Slim] Hey!

141
00:09:24,188 --> 00:09:25,314
Tidy it up in here!

142
00:09:25,398 --> 00:09:27,024
[Quincey] Our bad, Slim.

143
00:09:29,860 --> 00:09:31,279
Dang!

144
00:09:31,362 --> 00:09:34,031
This boy-boy got the face
beat off him!

145
00:09:34,115 --> 00:09:35,741
[Twin] They got him
for his Krispy Kremes too!

146
00:09:35,825 --> 00:09:37,159
[both laughing]

147
00:09:37,243 --> 00:09:38,452
[Slim] Hey, I'm not telling you again.

148
00:09:38,536 --> 00:09:40,121
[Quincey] Let us put
the gloves on then, man!

149
00:09:40,204 --> 00:09:43,040
-I teach boxing, not clowning.
-[Twin] We ready, Slim.

150
00:09:43,124 --> 00:09:44,667
Let us show you
these hands, big bruh.

151
00:09:44,750 --> 00:09:46,627
You all about that fight life, little guy.

152
00:09:47,587 --> 00:09:48,629
Come on, Slim!

153
00:09:48,713 --> 00:09:51,465
-Slim, please! We serious!
-We ready!

154
00:09:51,549 --> 00:09:52,675
[Slim] One condition.

155
00:09:53,926 --> 00:09:56,846
You take little Bruce Leroy here
under your wing.

156
00:09:56,929 --> 00:09:59,640
Every time you in the gym,
he in the gym with you.

157
00:09:59,724 --> 00:10:02,685
And if y'all ain't together,
nobody boxing.

158
00:10:02,768 --> 00:10:05,104
And you.
You walked him in here.

159
00:10:05,187 --> 00:10:08,065
I'm expecting you to help me
train him, Coach.

160
00:10:08,149 --> 00:10:10,943
-[softly] Whoa, he just said "Coach!"
-[Walt] Hey, man.

161
00:10:11,027 --> 00:10:13,779
I, uh, I came here
to use a computer.

162
00:10:13,863 --> 00:10:16,115
-I ain't no damn babysitter.
-I know who you are.

163
00:10:18,200 --> 00:10:20,328
Now, don't just be
coming here using.

164
00:10:20,411 --> 00:10:22,663
My philosophy, we pay it forward.

165
00:10:22,747 --> 00:10:25,041
You take, you give it back.

166
00:10:36,594 --> 00:10:38,429
Hey, good luck with that.

167
00:10:38,512 --> 00:10:40,514
[car horn blaring, traffic droning]

168
00:10:52,943 --> 00:10:55,154
Stay as long as you need, okay?

169
00:10:57,823 --> 00:10:59,784
-[door bell jingling]
-[Turk] Yo, Lee.

170
00:11:01,118 --> 00:11:02,286
Let me get a coffee.

171
00:11:03,579 --> 00:11:06,248
You know it's supposed to be me and you,
right, my beautiful queen?

172
00:11:06,332 --> 00:11:08,459
Your mouth stay talking slick, Turk.

173
00:11:08,542 --> 00:11:11,504
Then, tell me you still love me,
I'll give you a big tip.

174
00:11:11,587 --> 00:11:13,673
I'm gonna text Tisha,
tell her you in here getting fresh.

175
00:11:13,756 --> 00:11:14,965
Mm!

176
00:11:15,049 --> 00:11:16,258
Your beautiful self.

177
00:11:17,551 --> 00:11:19,553
-[♪ music playing faintly]
-[Turk sniffling]

178
00:11:22,765 --> 00:11:24,725
Walt! My dawg!

179
00:11:24,809 --> 00:11:26,185
What's good?

180
00:11:26,268 --> 00:11:27,853
You out, out?

181
00:11:27,937 --> 00:11:29,814
Uh, yeah. Early.

182
00:11:29,897 --> 00:11:31,440
Ah, they let you out early?

183
00:11:33,359 --> 00:11:34,568
Alright, Black man.

184
00:11:34,652 --> 00:11:35,820
It's good to see you. You straight?

185
00:11:35,903 --> 00:11:37,863
-Yeah, I'm cool.
-Alright.

186
00:11:38,739 --> 00:11:40,241
Hey, hey, uh, Turk.

187
00:11:46,706 --> 00:11:48,165
It's good to see you, man.

188
00:11:49,333 --> 00:11:51,127
Good to see you too, Walt.

189
00:11:51,210 --> 00:11:52,211
Be safe.

190
00:11:56,716 --> 00:11:57,717
Yo, Lee!

191
00:11:58,843 --> 00:12:00,594
-[Turk] Believe in us, babe.
-[Lee] Boy, bye.

192
00:12:00,678 --> 00:12:01,679
[Turk laughing]

193
00:12:02,722 --> 00:12:04,724
[paper rustling]

194
00:12:07,435 --> 00:12:08,519
Hey. Hey, Turk.

195
00:12:11,063 --> 00:12:13,357
Closed mouths don't get fed, Walt.
What up?

196
00:12:13,441 --> 00:12:15,693
Look, man, uh, if you could, uh,
if you could help me out, man,

197
00:12:15,776 --> 00:12:18,112
-I'd-- I'd really appreciate it.
-By the look at that penitentiary bag,

198
00:12:18,195 --> 00:12:20,740
it look like you looking for a place
to shit, shower, and shave.

199
00:12:23,492 --> 00:12:24,994
But I might be able to get you
a job on the crew.

200
00:12:25,995 --> 00:12:27,496
-You mean like a job, job?
-[Turk] Yeah.

201
00:12:27,580 --> 00:12:28,914
We always looking for guys.

202
00:12:28,998 --> 00:12:32,626
It's backbreaking work,
but get you a few dollars.

203
00:12:32,710 --> 00:12:34,628
Would you look out like that, man, for me?

204
00:12:34,712 --> 00:12:37,298
Man, Walt, you know how
much you mean to us, man?

205
00:12:38,090 --> 00:12:40,342
That gym, them kids,
you saved a lot of lives, man.

206
00:12:40,426 --> 00:12:42,887
So, if you asking me for help,
hell yeah, say less.

207
00:12:44,430 --> 00:12:47,308
Shit, when I got out,
it took me like a year to get shit going.

208
00:12:47,391 --> 00:12:49,435
You know?
We don't exist to them.

209
00:12:49,518 --> 00:12:51,020
I ain't trying to see
nobody go through that.

210
00:12:51,103 --> 00:12:52,062
Turk.

211
00:12:53,522 --> 00:12:54,523
Thank you, man.

212
00:12:54,607 --> 00:12:56,442
Yeah, man.
Look, you know I'ma ask you

213
00:12:56,525 --> 00:12:57,943
'cause everybody wondering.

214
00:12:59,069 --> 00:13:01,322
They gonna ask
the same thing, alright?

215
00:13:01,405 --> 00:13:03,574
You get them demons out
while you was in there?

216
00:13:03,657 --> 00:13:05,743
Hey, man, I'm beyond it.

217
00:13:05,826 --> 00:13:07,244
Three years.

218
00:13:07,328 --> 00:13:09,038
Alright, man.

219
00:13:09,121 --> 00:13:11,123
Hey, we working.

220
00:13:19,965 --> 00:13:22,968
[♪ brooding music playing]

221
00:13:44,156 --> 00:13:45,783
[car honks loudly]

222
00:14:01,215 --> 00:14:04,218
[♪ brooding music continues]

223
00:14:11,016 --> 00:14:12,351
[♪ music fades out]

224
00:14:14,019 --> 00:14:16,522
Gee me. Walt?

225
00:14:18,899 --> 00:14:19,900
Walt!

226
00:14:21,360 --> 00:14:22,820
-[chuckles]
-That's you!

227
00:14:22,903 --> 00:14:24,697
-Hey, yo, man.
-[sighs]

228
00:14:24,780 --> 00:14:26,282
Ain't nobody but me, man.

229
00:14:26,365 --> 00:14:27,783
[Coach Mac sighs]

230
00:14:28,868 --> 00:14:30,828
Walt, how come you ain't ring
on somebody's phone,

231
00:14:30,911 --> 00:14:32,413
tell somebody something?

232
00:14:32,496 --> 00:14:34,290
Man, you know
I don't wanna be no bother.

233
00:14:34,373 --> 00:14:35,499
Shit.

234
00:14:36,584 --> 00:14:40,045
You, uh, you got some--
somewhere to sleep?

235
00:14:40,129 --> 00:14:42,464
Since you're asking, I don't, Coach.

236
00:14:43,966 --> 00:14:46,844
I really, I think I just need
a couple days just to get myself right.

237
00:14:47,970 --> 00:14:49,221
If that's alright.

238
00:14:53,183 --> 00:14:54,184
Um, I'm...

239
00:14:55,436 --> 00:14:56,604
I'm sorry, Walt.

240
00:14:57,855 --> 00:14:59,940
She-- she ain't gonna allow it.

241
00:15:01,108 --> 00:15:02,860
-I understand.
-[Delores] Mac?

242
00:15:02,943 --> 00:15:04,612
Who is that?

243
00:15:04,695 --> 00:15:07,156
Uh, baby, it's, uh, that's-- it's Walt.

244
00:15:07,239 --> 00:15:08,365
Just got home.

245
00:15:09,867 --> 00:15:11,410
Hey, Miss Delores,
how you-- how you doing?

246
00:15:11,493 --> 00:15:13,495
So, what is it gonna be
this time, Walter?

247
00:15:14,455 --> 00:15:15,539
Take care of my son.

248
00:15:17,082 --> 00:15:18,417
Get my life together.

249
00:15:18,500 --> 00:15:21,045
I'm expecting you to keep your word.

250
00:15:22,546 --> 00:15:24,214
You ain't gotta tell me twice, Coach.

251
00:15:25,507 --> 00:15:28,052
Hey, it's good seeing you.

252
00:15:31,430 --> 00:15:32,556
-Alright.
-Alright.

253
00:15:38,812 --> 00:15:40,814
[footsteps approaching]

254
00:15:44,234 --> 00:15:45,736
[grunting]

255
00:15:48,530 --> 00:15:50,115
[Slim] Looks like you got that thing.

256
00:15:51,241 --> 00:15:52,326
What thing would that be?

257
00:15:52,409 --> 00:15:53,410
[exhales sharply]

258
00:15:56,330 --> 00:15:57,331
[box thuds]

259
00:15:58,374 --> 00:15:59,917
[Slim] Like you got nowhere to go.

260
00:16:03,087 --> 00:16:04,588
But this gym keeps calling you.

261
00:16:05,381 --> 00:16:06,924
How long they sit you down for?

262
00:16:09,176 --> 00:16:10,302
Gave me five.

263
00:16:11,303 --> 00:16:12,471
Did three and a half.

264
00:16:12,554 --> 00:16:13,555
Yeah.

265
00:16:15,975 --> 00:16:16,976
Well, heads up.

266
00:16:18,185 --> 00:16:19,436
Don't get too attached to this place.

267
00:16:20,521 --> 00:16:22,064
City budget cuts are coming,

268
00:16:22,147 --> 00:16:24,108
and ain't got too many places
for these kids to go.

269
00:16:24,191 --> 00:16:26,193
I'm doing the best I can
to keep the lights on.

270
00:16:28,654 --> 00:16:30,781
But they gonna close it.

271
00:16:31,323 --> 00:16:32,324
[Slim grunts]

272
00:16:33,450 --> 00:16:35,327
Just like they close everything else.

273
00:16:37,204 --> 00:16:38,372
You know, I'm guessing...

274
00:16:41,166 --> 00:16:43,544
you searching for answers
for yourself.

275
00:16:44,920 --> 00:16:46,505
I need a lot more than answers.

276
00:16:51,176 --> 00:16:54,388
We got a lot of guys
around here back from a bid...

277
00:16:55,889 --> 00:16:57,182
needing the computer.

278
00:16:59,601 --> 00:17:02,187
None of 'em
got the boxing knowledge you got.

279
00:17:02,271 --> 00:17:04,440
That's for sure. Ooh.

280
00:17:06,650 --> 00:17:07,901
Yeah.

281
00:17:09,903 --> 00:17:11,071
I'm guessing...

282
00:17:12,448 --> 00:17:15,951
you some type of valued asset.

283
00:17:16,035 --> 00:17:17,036
[Walt chuckles softly]

284
00:17:18,912 --> 00:17:21,331
-[chuckles] Crazy.
-Yeah. Yeah.

285
00:17:23,042 --> 00:17:24,043
Ahh.

286
00:17:25,502 --> 00:17:26,503
Come on.

287
00:17:30,132 --> 00:17:31,800
Welcome to the presidential suite.

288
00:17:32,676 --> 00:17:34,261
I sleep in here some nights.

289
00:17:35,262 --> 00:17:38,766
But I have a home, you don't.

290
00:17:40,017 --> 00:17:42,227
-[items thudding and sliding]
-[Slim grunting]

291
00:17:42,311 --> 00:17:44,688
Anything in that closet is yours.

292
00:17:46,732 --> 00:17:51,653
The locker room shower
and shitter in here gets it done.

293
00:17:53,489 --> 00:17:57,076
And it, uh, has a few...

294
00:17:58,952 --> 00:18:00,204
minutes left.

295
00:18:03,373 --> 00:18:04,374
[keys jingling]

296
00:18:06,960 --> 00:18:08,295
The only thing is...

297
00:18:11,173 --> 00:18:13,967
when I lock up for the night,
you in here till the morning.

298
00:18:14,051 --> 00:18:15,969
-We clear on that?
-Yeah.

299
00:18:18,222 --> 00:18:19,515
Thank you.

300
00:18:20,432 --> 00:18:21,433
Yeah.

301
00:18:27,189 --> 00:18:28,190
[door slams shut]

302
00:18:30,317 --> 00:18:32,486
[door lock clacking]

303
00:18:32,569 --> 00:18:35,155
[♪ gentle music playing]

304
00:18:40,119 --> 00:18:41,120
[wincing]

305
00:18:44,581 --> 00:18:46,083
[sighs]

306
00:18:51,797 --> 00:18:52,798
[grunts sharply]

307
00:18:55,759 --> 00:18:57,761
-[keys jingling]
-[door lock clacking]

308
00:19:00,097 --> 00:19:01,431
[light switch clicking]

309
00:19:03,976 --> 00:19:05,936
Top of the morning to you!
Let's roll.

310
00:19:06,019 --> 00:19:07,563
[Walt]
Man. [groaning]

311
00:19:07,646 --> 00:19:09,148
My back keeps locking up.

312
00:19:10,107 --> 00:19:12,568
-What time is it?
-Time for you to earn your keep.

313
00:19:12,651 --> 00:19:14,945
-That's what the clock say.
-[keys jingling]

314
00:19:15,028 --> 00:19:16,196
[whispering] Oh, man.

315
00:19:17,948 --> 00:19:19,074
[sighs]

316
00:19:20,617 --> 00:19:21,660
Shit.

317
00:19:21,743 --> 00:19:25,581
Hey, hey, man, I need to use
the computer lab real quick.

318
00:19:25,664 --> 00:19:27,249
[Slim] This ain't no internet cafe.

319
00:19:28,709 --> 00:19:31,211
Gym now, computer later.

320
00:19:32,171 --> 00:19:34,840
[Walt] Come on, bruh.
It's my life we talking about.

321
00:19:34,923 --> 00:19:36,049
[Slim] Yeah, I know.

322
00:19:39,469 --> 00:19:41,638
-[sweeper thuds]
-If you don't mind,

323
00:19:41,722 --> 00:19:43,390
place is a bit dusty.

324
00:19:43,473 --> 00:19:44,725
Man, I ain't no janitor.

325
00:19:44,808 --> 00:19:46,143
What?

326
00:19:46,226 --> 00:19:47,561
Room and board ain't free.

327
00:19:48,687 --> 00:19:49,897
We work around here.

328
00:19:54,902 --> 00:19:57,237
Fair exchange. Ain't no robbery.

329
00:20:00,282 --> 00:20:02,284
[Walt clicking tongue,
whispering indistinctly]

330
00:20:03,577 --> 00:20:04,912
[sucking teeth]

331
00:20:06,496 --> 00:20:08,248
[Ketta]
<i>How you adjusting, Peanut?</i>

332
00:20:08,332 --> 00:20:09,958
<i>You liking your teachers</i>
<i>and your classes?</i>

333
00:20:12,920 --> 00:20:14,671
What happened to your face?

334
00:20:15,714 --> 00:20:16,840
I got jumped.

335
00:20:18,592 --> 00:20:20,010
They stole my sneakers.

336
00:20:20,761 --> 00:20:22,179
[Ketta] Well, did you report it?

337
00:20:23,096 --> 00:20:24,806
Don't work like that, Miss Ketta.

338
00:20:24,890 --> 00:20:27,226
Best to keep your mouth shut
so you don't got no more problems.

339
00:20:27,309 --> 00:20:28,477
Young man, look at me.

340
00:20:29,436 --> 00:20:30,395
Look at me.

341
00:20:31,396 --> 00:20:33,649
In this life, win or lose,
you don't ever back down

342
00:20:33,732 --> 00:20:35,192
to somebody harming you,
you understand?

343
00:20:36,401 --> 00:20:38,362
-Yes, ma'am.
-Sometimes you gotta be a lion

344
00:20:38,445 --> 00:20:40,197
in order to be the lamb you are.

345
00:20:41,490 --> 00:20:43,325
You been able to make
any new friends?

346
00:20:43,408 --> 00:20:45,494
-There's some homies.
-[Ketta] Yeah? [chuckles]

347
00:20:45,577 --> 00:20:46,703
They seem cool.

348
00:20:48,705 --> 00:20:50,874
But it's hard, Miss Ketta.

349
00:20:50,958 --> 00:20:52,709
"No new friends" is real!

350
00:20:54,878 --> 00:20:56,421
Think I'm gonna try boxing.

351
00:20:56,505 --> 00:20:58,048
I know a little something about that.

352
00:20:59,174 --> 00:21:01,385
I believe you'd make
a good fighter, Peanut.

353
00:21:02,636 --> 00:21:03,804
[chuckles]

354
00:21:06,265 --> 00:21:07,975
There something else
you wanna run by me?

355
00:21:14,690 --> 00:21:16,733
How do I talk to girls?

356
00:21:35,711 --> 00:21:37,713
[computer keys clacking]

357
00:21:43,427 --> 00:21:46,305
[computer mouse sliding
and clicking]

358
00:21:54,187 --> 00:21:55,188
[computer chimes]

359
00:22:00,819 --> 00:22:02,904
-[footsteps approaching]
-[Walt exhales]

360
00:22:02,988 --> 00:22:04,072
[Slim] Word of advice.

361
00:22:05,699 --> 00:22:08,201
Checking that thing every hour
ain't gonna change your life overnight.

362
00:22:08,285 --> 00:22:11,038
You know, I did everything
you asked me to.

363
00:22:11,121 --> 00:22:13,165
You can save your lecture
for them young boys.

364
00:22:13,248 --> 00:22:14,499
I ain't your enemy.

365
00:22:16,293 --> 00:22:17,878
And neither are them kids.

366
00:22:22,716 --> 00:22:24,009
Lean in, Walt.

367
00:22:24,092 --> 00:22:25,344
[Walt sighs]

368
00:22:27,262 --> 00:22:29,473
Take a punch to give a punch.

369
00:22:29,556 --> 00:22:30,724
Remember...

370
00:22:34,144 --> 00:22:35,437
[sighs] Shit.

371
00:22:37,230 --> 00:22:38,398
-Alright.
-[Slim scoffs softly]

372
00:22:39,274 --> 00:22:40,817
...a watched clock never moves.

373
00:22:42,027 --> 00:22:43,570
[keys jingling]

374
00:22:44,446 --> 00:22:46,823
[clock ticking]

375
00:22:47,491 --> 00:22:50,494
[ticking continues]

376
00:22:52,537 --> 00:22:56,500
[ticking echoing]

377
00:22:58,794 --> 00:22:59,795
<i>-♪ Ay! ♪</i>
-[school bell ringing]

378
00:22:59,878 --> 00:23:01,129
[♪ "No Dayz Off"
by Kairo X Sha'Ki playing]

379
00:23:01,213 --> 00:23:02,923
<i>♪ We don't follow rules,</i>
<i>we not like the rest ♪</i>

380
00:23:03,006 --> 00:23:05,592
<i>♪ Type to break a record</i>
<i>and won't break a sweat ♪</i>

381
00:23:05,675 --> 00:23:07,511
<i>♪ Heard your last attempt,</i>
<i>we wasn't feeling that ♪</i>

382
00:23:07,594 --> 00:23:10,180
<i>♪ It's over, man, no novocaine,</i>
<i>it's time to bring the feeling back ♪</i>

383
00:23:10,263 --> 00:23:11,264
<i>♪ It's on ♪</i>

384
00:23:11,348 --> 00:23:12,933
<i>♪ Chilling in the future, we gone ♪</i>

385
00:23:13,016 --> 00:23:15,936
<i>♪ Sicker than penicillin,</i>
<i>you want it, you go and get it ♪</i>

386
00:23:16,019 --> 00:23:18,313
<i>♪ Till the end, never quitting,</i>
<i>something you gotta witness ♪</i>

387
00:23:18,397 --> 00:23:20,732
<i>♪ Gotta go make a difference,</i>
<i>gotta complete the mission ♪</i>

388
00:23:20,816 --> 00:23:21,817
<i>♪ It's done ♪</i>

389
00:23:21,900 --> 00:23:24,694
[Slim] Come on, spread out, spread out.
Right there, right there.

390
00:23:24,778 --> 00:23:26,321
Alright, decide what you gonna do.

391
00:23:26,405 --> 00:23:28,615
That's it. Good job, good job.

392
00:23:28,698 --> 00:23:31,701
[line ringing]

393
00:23:37,290 --> 00:23:39,668
[Ketta] [on voicemail] <i>Hey, it's Ketta.</i>
<i>Leave me a message.</i>

394
00:23:41,253 --> 00:23:43,213
[Slim] That's it, keep your balance.

395
00:23:44,089 --> 00:23:45,674
And back.

396
00:23:45,757 --> 00:23:47,134
Keep your balance, knees bent.

397
00:23:47,217 --> 00:23:48,844
That's it. That's it.

398
00:23:48,927 --> 00:23:50,429
Slip. Let me get a slip.

399
00:23:50,512 --> 00:23:52,180
That's good. There you go.

400
00:23:52,264 --> 00:23:53,807
Combination like that. Alright.

401
00:23:55,392 --> 00:23:56,685
Good balance.

402
00:23:56,768 --> 00:23:58,353
Keep your balance.
Keep your balance.

403
00:23:58,437 --> 00:23:59,438
Stop, center.

404
00:23:59,521 --> 00:24:00,605
Go back.

405
00:24:00,689 --> 00:24:02,315
To the center. That's it, and fold.

406
00:24:02,399 --> 00:24:04,151
Alright. Combo.

407
00:24:04,234 --> 00:24:05,235
[kids exhaling sharply]

408
00:24:05,318 --> 00:24:06,653
[Slim] Yeah, that's it.

409
00:24:06,736 --> 00:24:07,904
There you go. Back.

410
00:24:08,864 --> 00:24:09,865
Back and slip.

411
00:24:11,450 --> 00:24:12,701
Come on. Hook.

412
00:24:13,577 --> 00:24:14,995
Give me a combo. One, two.

413
00:24:15,078 --> 00:24:17,330
Keep your back. Back.

414
00:24:17,414 --> 00:24:19,291
And combo right there.

415
00:24:19,374 --> 00:24:20,542
And back up.

416
00:24:20,625 --> 00:24:22,919
Back, back, back.

417
00:24:23,003 --> 00:24:24,087
Back. Combo!

418
00:24:25,213 --> 00:24:26,298
One, two, three.

419
00:24:28,258 --> 00:24:29,968
Yo, what's up with janitor dude?

420
00:24:30,051 --> 00:24:31,970
[Slim] Time! Gather 'round.

421
00:24:36,224 --> 00:24:38,518
You have no idea who that man is.

422
00:24:38,602 --> 00:24:39,811
It ain't that serious, Slim.

423
00:24:39,895 --> 00:24:41,897
You act like he Bud Crawford
or somebody.

424
00:24:41,980 --> 00:24:43,106
[Slim] He wasn't no fighter.

425
00:24:43,190 --> 00:24:45,525
He was just the best boxing coach
Southeast has ever known.

426
00:24:45,609 --> 00:24:49,404
Now, I watched my old boxing film
and studied my books.

427
00:24:50,197 --> 00:24:54,117
But what Walt got,
you ain't gonna find in no books.

428
00:24:54,201 --> 00:24:59,414
His life is like one of them ESPN
30 for 30 documentaries, y'all.

429
00:24:59,498 --> 00:25:01,958
If he's so great,
why don't he train nobody no more?

430
00:25:02,042 --> 00:25:04,211
Bruh, that was a double negative
you just used.

431
00:25:04,294 --> 00:25:05,879
-So what?
-[Twin sighs]

432
00:25:05,962 --> 00:25:07,923
It ain't my place
to tell you his story.

433
00:25:11,384 --> 00:25:12,385
Hmm.

434
00:25:13,303 --> 00:25:15,639
Alright, that's it for today.

435
00:25:17,599 --> 00:25:19,142
Y'all got some badass feet.

436
00:25:19,226 --> 00:25:20,727
Go on home.

437
00:25:20,810 --> 00:25:23,188
Keep an eye on each other's back
when y'all hit that block.

438
00:25:23,271 --> 00:25:24,272
Go ahead.

439
00:25:30,153 --> 00:25:33,198
[running footsteps, sneakers squeaking]

440
00:25:36,201 --> 00:25:37,536
Lord have mercy.

441
00:25:43,542 --> 00:25:44,543
Hey.

442
00:25:44,626 --> 00:25:46,002
Slim say you used to be great.

443
00:25:47,170 --> 00:25:48,296
That true, OG?

444
00:25:49,798 --> 00:25:50,882
A long time ago.

445
00:25:52,509 --> 00:25:54,761
Nobody remembers the corner man,
just the fighter.

446
00:25:54,844 --> 00:25:56,221
I best, uh, keep it moving.

447
00:25:57,764 --> 00:26:00,850
Whatever happened to you,
I'm really sorry, Coach.

448
00:26:02,310 --> 00:26:03,728
Don't need to be sorry for me.

449
00:26:05,021 --> 00:26:07,190
And call me Walt. You?

450
00:26:07,274 --> 00:26:08,358
Peanut.

451
00:26:08,441 --> 00:26:09,818
[Walt] Peanut?
Why they call you Peanut?

452
00:26:10,944 --> 00:26:12,779
Oh, I see it now.

453
00:26:12,862 --> 00:26:14,447
[chuckles] Big-ass head.

454
00:26:14,531 --> 00:26:15,532
[Peanut chuckles]

455
00:26:15,991 --> 00:26:16,992
[Walt chuckles]

456
00:26:17,075 --> 00:26:18,702
[Peanut]
What you think about training me?

457
00:26:20,495 --> 00:26:22,080
I could be your next champion.

458
00:26:22,998 --> 00:26:26,126
Just stick with Slim,
he'll show you what to do.

459
00:26:26,209 --> 00:26:28,837
I done lost the love for it anyway,
but hey, hey.

460
00:26:30,255 --> 00:26:31,673
Ain't nothing wrong with you.

461
00:26:32,549 --> 00:26:33,675
Remember that.

462
00:26:35,343 --> 00:26:37,387
For someone who ain't interested
in boxing no more...

463
00:26:38,930 --> 00:26:40,348
then why you keep showing up?

464
00:26:42,017 --> 00:26:43,727
I mean, like,
your whole demeanor towards me

465
00:26:43,810 --> 00:26:45,312
is giving depressing at best, bruh.

466
00:26:46,396 --> 00:26:48,231
Give me the same energy
I give you, OG.

467
00:26:48,315 --> 00:26:49,899
-[door opens]
-[Twin and Quincey laughing]

468
00:26:51,651 --> 00:26:53,695
-Mm.
-Oh. This dude.

469
00:26:55,905 --> 00:26:59,492
How it look you some
sort of boxing legend

470
00:26:59,576 --> 00:27:00,827
cleaning shitty toilets?

471
00:27:00,910 --> 00:27:02,871
Hey, watch your mouth.

472
00:27:02,954 --> 00:27:04,581
Why don't you use
that same tough guy energy

473
00:27:04,664 --> 00:27:06,625
to watch your friend's back,
young muscles?

474
00:27:09,044 --> 00:27:11,796
Hey, ain't no disrespect, lil shorties.

475
00:27:13,632 --> 00:27:14,633
Alright.

476
00:27:17,052 --> 00:27:20,055
[♪ gentle music playing]

477
00:27:31,816 --> 00:27:33,568
[computer keys clacking]

478
00:27:34,027 --> 00:27:35,028
[computer chimes]

479
00:27:36,738 --> 00:27:38,406
[both exhaling sharply]

480
00:27:39,783 --> 00:27:41,284
-[line ringing]
-[Ketta]<i> Hey, it's Ketta.</i>

481
00:27:41,368 --> 00:27:43,119
<i>-Leave me a message.</i>
-[phone beeps]

482
00:27:43,203 --> 00:27:45,622
Ketta, call me back.
It's-- it's Walt.

483
00:27:45,705 --> 00:27:48,708
[♪ gentle music continues playing]

484
00:27:49,626 --> 00:27:51,628
[indistinct chatter, exhaling sharply]

485
00:27:52,879 --> 00:27:54,839
Hey, Ketta, it's-- it's me, Walt.

486
00:27:56,091 --> 00:27:57,842
I was hoping we could talk again.

487
00:27:59,344 --> 00:28:00,762
<i>I'm-- I'm trying.</i>

488
00:28:01,888 --> 00:28:03,223
[kids chattering]

489
00:28:09,813 --> 00:28:10,814
[sighs]

490
00:28:20,907 --> 00:28:22,909
[both exhaling sharply]

491
00:28:26,663 --> 00:28:28,331
Ketta, I love you.

492
00:28:29,249 --> 00:28:32,377
[♪ gentle music playing]

493
00:29:03,658 --> 00:29:04,659
[♪ music fades out]

494
00:29:07,495 --> 00:29:09,831
Walt, what you doing down here, man?

495
00:29:12,041 --> 00:29:13,042
Turk.

496
00:29:14,836 --> 00:29:17,922
Man, week after week, man,
I'm on that damn computer,

497
00:29:18,006 --> 00:29:20,175
and I still ain't found no job, man.

498
00:29:20,258 --> 00:29:22,510
Look, these things take time.
Something gonna open up, man.

499
00:29:22,594 --> 00:29:23,762
I'm sorry I don't got the answer for you,

500
00:29:23,845 --> 00:29:25,472
but you can't just be showing up
down here to my job.

501
00:29:25,555 --> 00:29:27,223
Hey, I ain't but one day away
from being on the street.

502
00:29:27,307 --> 00:29:28,975
-Look, I understand that--
-You said you was gonna help me,

503
00:29:29,058 --> 00:29:30,769
-man, what--
-Hey, man, calm down!

504
00:29:31,186 --> 00:29:32,187
[Walt exhales]

505
00:29:32,270 --> 00:29:33,730
-Hell wrong with you, Walt?
-Alright. My bad.

506
00:29:33,813 --> 00:29:34,814
Stay positive!

507
00:29:36,149 --> 00:29:37,776
I don't need this from you.

508
00:29:37,859 --> 00:29:39,986
The minute one of these good old
white boys say something you don't like,

