00:40:18,499 --> 00:40:20,751
-What's going on with your back, man?
-Feel like needles in there, man.

747
00:40:20,835 --> 00:40:23,462
You move any slower in here,
you ain't gonna be no good.

748
00:40:23,546 --> 00:40:25,548
And if you ain't no good,
they gonna let you go.

749
00:40:26,757 --> 00:40:28,759
Man, I ain't-- I ain't trying
to mess up your situation.

750
00:40:28,843 --> 00:40:31,387
-No, you need to go see my doctor.
-Yeah, with what health insurance?

751
00:40:31,470 --> 00:40:32,763
It's a free clinic.

752
00:40:34,432 --> 00:40:37,435
[muffled whirring]

753
00:40:38,519 --> 00:40:40,187
-[phone ringing]
-[secretary] Walter Manigan?

754
00:40:42,773 --> 00:40:44,275
[doctor]
<i>Describe the pain for me.</i>

755
00:40:45,067 --> 00:40:46,110
Like a knife in my back.

756
00:40:46,193 --> 00:40:47,194
[inhales sharply]

757
00:40:47,862 --> 00:40:50,322
The pain shoot down through my right leg
and down into my foot.

758
00:40:51,782 --> 00:40:53,617
Can hardly get my shoe on
some mornings.

759
00:40:54,577 --> 00:40:56,495
-Does it feel electrical?
-Mm-hmm.

760
00:40:56,579 --> 00:40:59,331
Like a... burning heat.

761
00:41:01,333 --> 00:41:02,334
Okay.

762
00:41:04,837 --> 00:41:06,922
You have sciatic nerve pain.

763
00:41:08,048 --> 00:41:10,759
-Sound like surgery to me.
-Well, it's about a 50/50.

764
00:41:10,843 --> 00:41:13,762
First, we have to get the inflammation
and damage you've caused down.

765
00:41:15,264 --> 00:41:17,850
-We'll start with methylprednisone.
-Hey, Doc, Doc.

766
00:41:17,933 --> 00:41:19,685
-You should know--
-I should know what?

767
00:41:21,187 --> 00:41:22,146
I got...

768
00:41:23,606 --> 00:41:25,191
I got over three years clean.

769
00:41:26,066 --> 00:41:28,402
And I'd rather stay in pain
than to jeopardize that.

770
00:41:33,324 --> 00:41:34,658
[pharmacist]
<i>Walter Manigan?</i>

771
00:41:36,202 --> 00:41:38,537
-You're Walter Manigan?
-I am.

772
00:41:38,621 --> 00:41:40,039
Prescription's ready.

773
00:41:41,832 --> 00:41:43,834
Be careful with those.

774
00:41:43,918 --> 00:41:46,921
[♪ somber music playing]

775
00:42:02,937 --> 00:42:03,896
[sighs]

776
00:42:12,905 --> 00:42:15,908
[♪ somber music continues playing]

777
00:42:37,930 --> 00:42:40,516
[whispering indistinctly]

778
00:43:00,411 --> 00:43:02,037
[door opens]

779
00:43:02,997 --> 00:43:03,998
[door closes]

780
00:43:17,094 --> 00:43:20,139
I spent the last three
and a half years of my life

781
00:43:20,222 --> 00:43:21,890
living in a silent grief.

782
00:43:27,730 --> 00:43:29,732
[inhales deeply]

783
00:43:29,815 --> 00:43:34,361
All that guilt from Little Walt's death
had never left me.

784
00:43:36,905 --> 00:43:40,200
I gave all my time to boxing.

785
00:43:41,744 --> 00:43:42,911
Not enough to him.

786
00:43:44,538 --> 00:43:45,748
To bringing him up right.

787
00:43:45,831 --> 00:43:48,709
I left it to you to do
that all by yourself, I...

788
00:43:51,337 --> 00:43:52,796
For that, I am truly sorry.

789
00:43:58,802 --> 00:43:59,970
Just please...

790
00:44:01,680 --> 00:44:03,515
Please tell me
you still believe in us.

791
00:44:04,933 --> 00:44:07,936
[♪ heartfelt music playing]

792
00:44:50,396 --> 00:44:52,147
-[Peanut] Ma!
-[Peanut's mom] Hey!

793
00:44:52,231 --> 00:44:55,275
-[Peanut] I got us some pizza.
-[Peanut's mom] Oh, okay! Thank you!

794
00:44:56,235 --> 00:44:58,278
Your father came by
looking for you today.

795
00:44:59,655 --> 00:45:00,656
For real?

796
00:45:01,448 --> 00:45:02,449
How'd he look?

797
00:45:04,660 --> 00:45:05,744
He looked fine.

798
00:45:08,330 --> 00:45:09,498
Peanut, um...

799
00:45:11,166 --> 00:45:12,418
he's a good person.

800
00:45:13,877 --> 00:45:17,339
Just... some people get stuck.

801
00:45:19,174 --> 00:45:21,301
How come you never say
anything bad about him?

802
00:45:22,970 --> 00:45:24,972
Now, what good is that gonna do you?

803
00:45:25,055 --> 00:45:26,056
You...

804
00:45:27,015 --> 00:45:29,518
are a sweet, selfless soul.

805
00:45:29,601 --> 00:45:31,979
It won't be long
before them fast little girls

806
00:45:32,062 --> 00:45:35,023
come chasing after
my perfect gentleman.

807
00:45:35,107 --> 00:45:36,859
Lord, help me.

808
00:45:38,402 --> 00:45:39,403
Uh...

809
00:45:40,487 --> 00:45:41,488
Excuse me.

810
00:45:42,197 --> 00:45:44,158
Wait, you got a girlfriend now?

811
00:45:44,241 --> 00:45:47,619
No, but I'm working on it,
so not <i>yet.</i>

812
00:45:47,703 --> 00:45:50,247
I ain't even take her
on a date yet!

813
00:45:50,330 --> 00:45:54,251
But I got plans, Ma.
She smiled at me.

814
00:45:55,711 --> 00:45:57,671
[chuckles] And what did you do?

815
00:45:57,755 --> 00:46:00,799
-I hit her with my finishing move.
-Your finishing move?

816
00:46:00,883 --> 00:46:02,342
Yeah, like this.

817
00:46:03,927 --> 00:46:05,596
Oh! [chuckles] P, come on.

818
00:46:05,679 --> 00:46:07,848
Just be yourself.

819
00:46:09,141 --> 00:46:10,893
Ask her out on a date first.

820
00:46:10,976 --> 00:46:12,227
[car door slams loudly]

821
00:46:13,729 --> 00:46:15,230
[groaning softly]

822
00:46:22,738 --> 00:46:24,198
[Slim] You doing alright down there?

823
00:46:26,408 --> 00:46:27,701
Yeah, just my back.

824
00:46:28,786 --> 00:46:29,870
Nothing new.

825
00:46:30,746 --> 00:46:32,331
You still gotta earn their trust.

826
00:46:32,414 --> 00:46:34,374
They seeing you every day
and you giving 'em your time

827
00:46:34,458 --> 00:46:36,502
is the first step. But now?

828
00:46:38,295 --> 00:46:39,797
It's them knowing your story.

829
00:46:41,006 --> 00:46:42,090
I don't know, man.

830
00:46:42,174 --> 00:46:43,801
Yeah, you just gotta
give it to 'em straight.

831
00:46:43,884 --> 00:46:46,220
Any one of these kids wanna know
how I fucked everything up,

832
00:46:46,303 --> 00:46:49,473
all they gotta do
is go on the internet, man.

833
00:46:49,556 --> 00:46:52,893
They don't need to sit around
listening to me tell some old sad story.

834
00:46:52,976 --> 00:46:55,604
Well, they'll respect you
if you come clean about your past, Walt.

835
00:46:55,687 --> 00:46:56,688
[softly] No, man.

836
00:46:58,649 --> 00:47:01,568
The moment you do that, watch.

837
00:47:05,405 --> 00:47:07,658
-God got plans for ya.
-[chuckles]

838
00:47:07,741 --> 00:47:09,201
[♪ uplifting music playing]

839
00:47:09,284 --> 00:47:11,995
[Slim] Oh, you got that easy.
We need to put another 24-inch up there.

840
00:47:13,664 --> 00:47:15,374
Alright.

841
00:47:15,457 --> 00:47:17,459
That's it. Keep your form.

842
00:47:18,710 --> 00:47:19,711
Keep your form.

843
00:47:23,966 --> 00:47:25,300
That's it, that's it.

844
00:47:25,384 --> 00:47:26,385
Go!

845
00:47:28,470 --> 00:47:29,513
Down and up!

846
00:47:31,473 --> 00:47:35,185
You know, I've been asking God
to send me my help for a long time.

847
00:47:36,937 --> 00:47:38,021
And sure enough...

848
00:47:40,107 --> 00:47:43,694
one day, this man right here
come walking in.

849
00:47:45,404 --> 00:47:46,780
That ain't no coincidence.

850
00:47:47,614 --> 00:47:49,491
That's divine intervention.

851
00:47:49,575 --> 00:47:51,952
Any of you know
what I'm talking about?

852
00:47:53,078 --> 00:47:54,580
It's when the universe,

853
00:47:54,663 --> 00:47:56,790
when God got bigger plans
for you, ain't it, Coach?

854
00:47:56,874 --> 00:47:58,834
Yeah! Oh!

855
00:47:58,917 --> 00:48:00,794
You sounding like Marcus Garvey.
Yeah.

856
00:48:02,087 --> 00:48:03,213
Well, I want y'all to hear...

857
00:48:05,007 --> 00:48:06,842
what divine intervention sounds like.

858
00:48:09,678 --> 00:48:10,888
Coach?

859
00:48:10,971 --> 00:48:13,974
[♪ compelling music playing]

860
00:48:24,902 --> 00:48:26,236
Alright, um...

861
00:48:28,989 --> 00:48:31,199
[clearing throat]
Um, I know there's been a lot of questions

862
00:48:31,283 --> 00:48:32,743
going around the gym about me.

863
00:48:36,246 --> 00:48:37,414
And, um...

864
00:48:39,374 --> 00:48:41,209
in order to win, can't be no secrets
between the fighter

865
00:48:41,293 --> 00:48:43,295
and his-- and his coach.

866
00:48:45,505 --> 00:48:47,758
So, y'all go ahead
and ask what you want.

867
00:48:47,841 --> 00:48:49,217
I'm a open book.

868
00:48:49,301 --> 00:48:50,761
Why'd you go to prison?

869
00:48:52,095 --> 00:48:53,096
Drugs.

870
00:48:53,889 --> 00:48:55,307
Selling 'em and using 'em.

871
00:48:57,851 --> 00:48:59,895
Y'all probably wonder why
if I know so much about boxing,

872
00:48:59,978 --> 00:49:01,688
it took me so long
to give you what I got.

873
00:49:04,524 --> 00:49:05,901
My son, he, uh...

874
00:49:07,527 --> 00:49:09,321
he got killed on his 18th birthday...

875
00:49:10,906 --> 00:49:12,366
following in my footsteps.

876
00:49:14,785 --> 00:49:17,412
Not a day go by
that I don't blame myself for his death.

877
00:49:18,121 --> 00:49:20,707
And when I look at y'all, I see him.

878
00:49:22,334 --> 00:49:23,919
What he could have become.

879
00:49:24,002 --> 00:49:26,421
I see y'all becoming men,
and he ain't get that chance

880
00:49:26,505 --> 00:49:28,423
'cause I failed as a father.

881
00:49:32,928 --> 00:49:34,388
Never thought I'd say this, but...

882
00:49:37,224 --> 00:49:39,726
I think God gave me
my purpose back in this gym.

883
00:49:41,770 --> 00:49:44,022
So, you done found
Jesus overnight, Coach?

884
00:49:44,106 --> 00:49:45,482
I found my fight again.

885
00:49:47,693 --> 00:49:49,069
It's in each and every one of y'all.

886
00:49:49,152 --> 00:49:53,031
Back in the day,
DC would always compete

887
00:49:53,115 --> 00:49:54,992
at the regionals
and junior nationals

888
00:49:55,075 --> 00:49:56,994
down in West Virginia.

889
00:49:57,077 --> 00:49:58,829
I'll make a deal with you.

890
00:49:58,912 --> 00:50:00,622
If y'all can see past my mistakes...

891
00:50:01,665 --> 00:50:03,583
I promise you I'll give you
everything I got.

892
00:50:04,668 --> 00:50:08,839
And each and every last one of y'all
will be in every fight until the end.

893
00:50:11,717 --> 00:50:14,052
-That alright?
-[all] Yes, Coach!

894
00:50:14,136 --> 00:50:15,512
-That alright?
-Yes, Coach!

895
00:50:15,595 --> 00:50:16,930
-[Walt] Lock in!
-Lock in!

896
00:50:17,014 --> 00:50:19,141
-[Walt] Lock in! Lock in!
-Lock in! Lock in!

897
00:50:19,224 --> 00:50:20,475
[Walt] Let's go! Come on!

898
00:50:20,559 --> 00:50:22,477
-[all clapping]
-[Slim] Yeah, you alright.

899
00:50:26,273 --> 00:50:28,275
[Walt] Get loose. Let your hands go.

900
00:50:31,695 --> 00:50:33,697
-[kids chattering]
-[sneaker squeaking]

901
00:50:37,325 --> 00:50:39,870
Hey, park that right hand right there.
One, two, three!

902
00:50:39,953 --> 00:50:41,705
Boom! One, two, three, two!

903
00:50:41,788 --> 00:50:43,707
Boom!
One, two, three, two!

904
00:50:43,790 --> 00:50:46,043
That's what I'm talking about.
One, two, one, two!

905
00:50:46,126 --> 00:50:47,627
One, two, one, two!

906
00:50:47,711 --> 00:50:49,755
Turn around, come back this way.

907
00:50:49,838 --> 00:50:51,465
Hey.

908
00:50:51,548 --> 00:50:52,632
Listen here.

909
00:50:55,552 --> 00:50:57,763
Y'all have to understand
these combinations like breathing.

910
00:50:57,846 --> 00:50:59,765
-Slip
-[all] [softly] Yes, Coach.

911
00:50:59,848 --> 00:51:01,558
-You hear me? Slip. Alright.
-[all] Yes, Coach!

912
00:51:01,641 --> 00:51:03,101
Duck!

913
00:51:03,185 --> 00:51:05,103
Duck! [grunts] Slip!

914
00:51:05,187 --> 00:51:07,189
Alright, fellas. [grunting]

915
00:51:07,272 --> 00:51:08,440
Welcome to the phone booth.

916
00:51:09,191 --> 00:51:10,859
Come on. P, Q, get up here.

917
00:51:10,942 --> 00:51:12,235
Left foot in.

918
00:51:12,319 --> 00:51:15,113
Get in your boxing stance.
Hands up, bend your knees.

919
00:51:15,197 --> 00:51:17,449
Alright, I wanna see you pivot.
Come on, turn.

920
00:51:17,532 --> 00:51:18,617
Alright, again.

921
00:51:19,534 --> 00:51:20,577
Again.

922
00:51:20,660 --> 00:51:21,953
Stay balanced, man.
Stay balanced.

923
00:51:22,037 --> 00:51:23,080
Again.

924
00:51:23,163 --> 00:51:24,748
Boom. Again, one more time.

925
00:51:24,831 --> 00:51:26,083
One, two, three, two.

926
00:51:27,042 --> 00:51:28,210
Now, the numbers are the code.

927
00:51:28,293 --> 00:51:30,462
You master the code,
you master your opponent.

928
00:51:30,545 --> 00:51:31,922
Down. Up!

929
00:51:32,798 --> 00:51:34,466
Pull. Pull.

930
00:51:34,549 --> 00:51:36,635
Turn it over. One, two, one, two!

931
00:51:36,718 --> 00:51:38,095
One, two, one, two!

932
00:51:38,178 --> 00:51:40,639
Work, work.
Get 'em up, get 'em up, get 'em up!

933
00:51:40,722 --> 00:51:42,390
Y'all gotta own the ring.

934
00:51:42,474 --> 00:51:44,184
-Say it with me, own the ring.
-[all] Own the ring!

935
00:51:44,267 --> 00:51:45,560
-Own the ring!
-[all] Own the ring!

936
00:51:46,603 --> 00:51:48,438
[Walt] You may hate my methods,
but you gonna love the results.

937
00:51:48,522 --> 00:51:49,773
Keep 'em up. Keep 'em up.

938
00:51:49,856 --> 00:51:51,691
Keep 'em up. Work, work, work!

939
00:51:51,775 --> 00:51:55,070
No fighter in the last round
is gonna outlast us, you hear me?

940
00:51:55,153 --> 00:51:56,738
[all] Yes, Coach!

941
00:51:56,822 --> 00:51:58,448
Pain makes perfection, men.

942
00:51:58,532 --> 00:51:59,950
-You hear me?
-[all] Yes, Coach!

943
00:52:00,033 --> 00:52:01,535
[Walt] You will commit!

944
00:52:01,618 --> 00:52:03,411
Day by day. Two, five, two!

945
00:52:03,495 --> 00:52:04,955
Brick by brick. Work. Up!

946
00:52:05,038 --> 00:52:06,414
The only question is...
Down!

947
00:52:06,498 --> 00:52:07,499
...will you lock in?
Work!

948
00:52:07,582 --> 00:52:09,501
-Yep. Lock in.
-[all] Lock in!

949
00:52:09,584 --> 00:52:10,627
-Lock in!
-[all] Lock in!

950
00:52:10,710 --> 00:52:11,711
Come on.

951
00:52:11,795 --> 00:52:13,338
-Lock in.
-[all] Lock in.

952
00:52:13,421 --> 00:52:14,673
-[Walt] Lock in!
-Lock in!

953
00:52:14,756 --> 00:52:16,091
-Lock in!
-[all] Lock in!

954
00:52:18,176 --> 00:52:20,595
{\an8}Felicia Ashley here live in Southeast DC

955
00:52:20,679 --> 00:52:22,806
{\an8}with Slim Richardson
and Walt Manigan, and the boys

956
00:52:22,889 --> 00:52:24,766
{\an8}-of the Congress Park Rec Center...
-Bricks up!

957
00:52:24,850 --> 00:52:27,811
{\an8}...after a quite unique
and odd training method...

958
00:52:27,894 --> 00:52:29,980
{\an8}-Yes.
-...with bricks of all things. Now, Slim.

959
00:52:30,063 --> 00:52:31,064
{\an8}-Yeah.
-Explain this to me.

960
00:52:31,148 --> 00:52:32,983
[Slim]<i> Yeah, well, they're tearing down</i>
<i>our communities</i>

961
00:52:33,066 --> 00:52:35,861
<i>and, uh, a-and rebuilding,</i>
<i>pushing the kids out.</i>

962
00:52:35,944 --> 00:52:38,738
<i>We training real hard for this</i>
<i>big tournament up in West Virginia,</i>

963
00:52:38,822 --> 00:52:41,908
<i>so we just trying to get as much</i>
<i>attention as we can for the boys.</i>

964
00:52:41,992 --> 00:52:44,411
<i>Get the whole city behind it.</i>

965
00:52:44,494 --> 00:52:46,788
[Felicia] <i>And Walt, what about you?</i>
<i>I mean, bricks.</i>

966
00:52:46,872 --> 00:52:48,456
[Walt] <i>Yeah, that's right.</i>
<i>Me and Slim,</i>

967
00:52:48,540 --> 00:52:50,792
{\an8}<i>we see it as a real opportunity</i>
<i>for the boys.</i>

968
00:52:50,876 --> 00:52:52,586
{\an8}<i>Uh, you know, so...</i>

969
00:52:52,669 --> 00:52:55,088
{\an8}<i>Hey, hey, hey, fellas, come over here!</i>
<i>Circle up!</i>

970
00:52:55,172 --> 00:52:56,590
{\an8}<i>-You know, one man's trash...</i>
<i>-Come on.</i>

971
00:52:56,673 --> 00:52:58,049
{\an8}<i>...is another man's treasure</i>
<i>kind of thing.</i>

972
00:52:58,133 --> 00:53:00,760
{\an8}<i>So, we got all the bricks we can find</i>
<i>and, uh, you know,</i>

973
00:53:00,844 --> 00:53:03,263
{\an8}<i>using 'em to build</i>
<i>our boys' foundations with 'em.</i>

974
00:53:03,346 --> 00:53:04,890
{\an8}<i>-Lock in!</i>
-[all] <i>Southeast!</i>

975
00:53:04,973 --> 00:53:07,184
{\an8}<i>-Lock in! Lock in!</i>
<i>-Southeast! Southeast!</i>

976
00:53:07,267 --> 00:53:08,393
{\an8}<i>Yeah.</i>

977
00:53:08,476 --> 00:53:09,895
{\an8}<i>Alright, well,</i>
<i>there you have it, everyone.</i>

978
00:53:09,978 --> 00:53:12,022
{\an8}<i>Live in Southeast DC,</i>
<i>training with bricks,</i>

979
00:53:12,105 --> 00:53:14,024
<i>Felicia Ashley DC17.</i>

980
00:53:25,785 --> 00:53:27,287
[knocking softly]

981
00:53:32,542 --> 00:53:34,544
[muffled footsteps approaching]

982
00:53:37,589 --> 00:53:39,132
[door opens]

983
00:53:44,095 --> 00:53:47,098
[♪ soft music playing]

984
00:53:59,611 --> 00:54:02,197
{\an8}Welcome to the Junior Regionals
Boxing Tournament.

985
00:54:02,280 --> 00:54:05,033
{\an8}Young amateur fighters
are stepping into the ring today

986
00:54:05,116 --> 00:54:07,160
{\an8}displaying pure heart and hustle.

987
00:54:07,244 --> 00:54:09,454
<i>Now, whoever's lucky enough</i>
<i>to advance today</i>

988
00:54:09,537 --> 00:54:12,791
<i>will be eligible to fight</i>
<i>in the Junior National Invitational</i>

989
00:54:12,874 --> 00:54:14,417
<i>in Charleston, West Virginia.</i>

990
00:54:14,501 --> 00:54:17,379
<i>♪ What you do it for?</i>
<i>If you ain't tryna get it up ♪</i>

991
00:54:17,462 --> 00:54:20,465
<i>♪ What you pursue it for?</i>
<i>If you ain't in it for the top ♪</i>

992
00:54:20,548 --> 00:54:23,593
<i>♪ Then what you shooting for?</i>
<i>If you ain't playing for my team ♪</i>

993
00:54:23,677 --> 00:54:25,512
[Michael Eaves]
<i>Now, for these coaches,</i>

994
00:54:25,595 --> 00:54:28,098
<i>it's a razor thin line</i>
<i>between winning...</i>

995
00:54:28,181 --> 00:54:30,600
-[bell dinging]
-[cheering and applause]

996
00:54:30,684 --> 00:54:31,685
<i>...and losing.</i>

997
00:54:33,436 --> 00:54:36,231
<i>And for the kids, well,</i>
<i>they're the pride of their cities.</i>

998
00:54:36,314 --> 00:54:40,151
<i>And many of these young competitors</i>
<i>are just starting their boxing careers.</i>

999
00:54:40,235 --> 00:54:43,071
<i>At this level,</i>
<i>it's not always about winning</i>

1000
00:54:43,154 --> 00:54:46,199
<i>as much as it is about</i>
<i>showing up to compete.</i>

1001
00:54:46,283 --> 00:54:47,993
<i>♪ Yeah, push on that vision,</i>
<i>I crafted the recipe ♪</i>

1002
00:54:48,076 --> 00:54:49,828
<i>♪ Step to that mission,</i>
<i>complacent I'll never be ♪</i>

1003
00:54:49,911 --> 00:54:51,538
<i>♪ Nah, nah, nah, nah,</i>
<i>there's sense in the duel ♪</i>

1004
00:54:51,621 --> 00:54:52,956
<i>♪ Kill everything</i>
<i>till I'm charged with a felony ♪</i>

1005
00:54:53,039 --> 00:54:54,332
Hey, focus.

1006
00:54:54,416 --> 00:54:55,625
It's you.

1007
00:54:55,709 --> 00:54:57,252
It's you, man. That's it!

1008
00:54:57,335 --> 00:54:58,336
Alright? Breathe in.

1009
00:54:58,420 --> 00:54:59,671
[inhales deeply]
Let it out slow.

1010
00:55:00,588 --> 00:55:02,299
{\an8}[Michael]
<i>Each bout is three rounds</i>

1011
00:55:02,382 --> 00:55:04,342
{\an8}<i>with a one-minute rest in between.</i>

1012
00:55:04,426 --> 00:55:05,427
{\an8}<i>Fighters score points...</i>

1013
00:55:05,510 --> 00:55:07,012
{\an8}-Fight!
<i>-...with clean punches to the front</i>

1014
00:55:07,095 --> 00:55:09,931
{\an8}<i>and sides of the head and body.</i>

1015
00:55:10,015 --> 00:55:11,433
<i>No shot below the belts,</i>

1016
00:55:11,516 --> 00:55:14,728
<i>no holding, and no hitting</i>
<i>after the break.</i>

1017
00:55:14,811 --> 00:55:16,354
[Slim] Alright, alright.
Pivot! Pivot on it!

1018
00:55:16,438 --> 00:55:18,315
Pivot on it! Yeah, that's it!

1019
00:55:18,398 --> 00:55:19,649
Throw that jab!

1020
00:55:19,733 --> 00:55:22,277
Keep your hands up!
Keep your hands up, that's it!

1021
00:55:22,360 --> 00:55:24,362
Turn him! Turn him, turn him!

1022
00:55:24,446 --> 00:55:26,573
-Hands up, hands up!
-[grunting]

1023
00:55:26,656 --> 00:55:28,491
[Slim] That's it, that's it!

1024
00:55:28,575 --> 00:55:29,826
[Walt] Let's go, Peanut!

1025
00:55:31,161 --> 00:55:32,787
[Slim] Peanut, go right back at his ass!

1026
00:55:32,871 --> 00:55:35,123
Broad stance,
and then shoot that brick!

1027
00:55:35,206 --> 00:55:37,375
[Walt] Stay locked in, P.
Stay locked in. You got this.

1028
00:55:37,459 --> 00:55:38,752
[Slim] Your body shots are crushing!

1029
00:55:39,627 --> 00:55:41,046
Twin, get up on that kid!

1030
00:55:41,129 --> 00:55:42,756
-Get up on that kid!
-[grunting]

1031
00:55:42,839 --> 00:55:45,383
Q, let your hands go, man, come on!

1032
00:55:45,467 --> 00:55:47,427
[Walt] Get up to the body.
To the body!

1033
00:55:47,510 --> 00:55:48,553
Come on, man!

1034
00:55:48,636 --> 00:55:50,972
-[grunting]
-Smoke that kid!

1035
00:55:51,639 --> 00:55:52,807
-[loud thud]
-[Twin groans]

1036
00:55:52,891 --> 00:55:54,059
[crowd reacting]

1037
00:55:55,101 --> 00:55:56,686
[referee] Seven! Eight!

1038
00:55:57,520 --> 00:55:58,897
{\an8}-[Slim] Alright, that's it.
-[bell dinging]

1039
00:55:58,980 --> 00:56:00,648
[Walt] Alright, go. Stay disciplined!

1040
00:56:00,732 --> 00:56:02,150
[Slim] That's it! That's it!

1041
00:56:02,233 --> 00:56:03,485
[bell dinging]

1042
00:56:03,568 --> 00:56:05,070
[referee] Alright, good round.

1043
00:56:05,487 --> 00:56:07,781
You think speed, alright?
We talked about this.

1044
00:56:07,864 --> 00:56:10,367
Hey, hey.
Get your money and be gone.

1045
00:56:10,450 --> 00:56:11,618
Stop looping your punches, man.

1046
00:56:11,701 --> 00:56:12,744
Straight shots.

1047
00:56:12,827 --> 00:56:13,828
[grunting]

1048
00:56:14,537 --> 00:56:16,164
Focus. [hitting mat]
I wanna see that dog

1049
00:56:16,247 --> 00:56:17,457
come out, you hear me?

1050
00:56:17,540 --> 00:56:18,958
-[gloves thwacking]
-[Slim] That's it, Q!

1051
00:56:19,042 --> 00:56:20,377
Yeah! Yeah, that's it!
That's what I'm talking about!

1052
00:56:20,460 --> 00:56:22,504
Shit, he ain't got nothing on you.

1053
00:56:22,587 --> 00:56:23,922
Get up on that kid.
Get up on that kid.

1054
00:56:24,005 --> 00:56:25,924
-Get in there.
-Throw your hands!

1055
00:56:26,007 --> 00:56:27,675
-[bell dinging]
-[referee] Time! Time!

1056
00:56:27,759 --> 00:56:29,427
Come on, come on, Peanut, tap in.

1057
00:56:30,220 --> 00:56:32,305
Listen, when they got 10 seconds,
you gotta let your hands go.

1058
00:56:32,389 --> 00:56:33,390
But that's good.

1059
00:56:33,473 --> 00:56:35,683
-Come on. You're in good shape.
-Yeah.

1060
00:56:35,767 --> 00:56:38,269
-[♪ expectant music playing]
-[crowd cheering]

1061
00:56:38,353 --> 00:56:40,688
Good job. Yeah.
That's what I'm talking about. Good job.

1062
00:56:42,899 --> 00:56:45,193
[announcer]
<i>And the winner is...</i>

1063
00:56:46,986 --> 00:56:48,780
And in the red corner,

1064
00:56:48,863 --> 00:56:52,367
representing Southeast DC,

1065
00:56:52,450 --> 00:56:54,327
Congress Park Rec,

1066
00:56:54,411 --> 00:56:56,830
-Quincey Williams!
-Yes! Yes!

1067
00:56:56,913 --> 00:56:58,373
[cheering and applause]

1068
00:56:58,456 --> 00:57:01,501
Raghaleek "Peanut" Bartee!

1069
00:57:01,584 --> 00:57:03,837
-[cheering and applause]
-[Walt thumping canvas]

1070
00:57:05,296 --> 00:57:06,464
Hell yeah.

1071
00:57:07,924 --> 00:57:09,926
[cheering and applause continues]

1072
00:57:10,009 --> 00:57:11,761
Told you, man. You got this.

1073
00:57:11,845 --> 00:57:16,057
{\an8}Look, some of these kids,
they just enjoy the sport, right?

1074
00:57:16,141 --> 00:57:18,101
{\an8}They love amateur boxing.

1075
00:57:18,184 --> 00:57:21,020
{\an8}But then, you got those other kids
that got that dog in them, you know?

1076
00:57:21,104 --> 00:57:23,606
{\an8}-[chuckles] That's right.
-Kinda like I had when I was coming up.

1077
00:57:23,690 --> 00:57:25,316
{\an8}I mean, but this is USA boxing.

1078
00:57:25,400 --> 00:57:27,861
{\an8}-That's right.
-And it all starts here.

1079
00:57:27,944 --> 00:57:31,114
{\an8}And I'm gonna tell you what
the great Iron Mike Tyson said to me.

1080
00:57:31,197 --> 00:57:32,198
{\an8}[chuckles]

1081
00:57:32,282 --> 00:57:35,368
{\an8}"Everybody's got a plan until
you get punched in the mouth."

1082
00:57:35,452 --> 00:57:36,453
[door closes]

1083
00:57:46,504 --> 00:57:49,674
[♪ tense, somber music playing]

1084
00:57:54,304 --> 00:57:57,307
[♪ somber music continues playing]

1085
00:57:57,390 --> 00:57:59,392
[monitors beeping]

1086
00:58:02,395 --> 00:58:04,355
[breathing heavily]

1087
00:58:09,027 --> 00:58:11,029
[indistinct chatter]

1088
00:58:14,407 --> 00:58:16,951
-Welcome back.
-Hey, baby.

1089
00:58:17,035 --> 00:58:18,286
[Wop Wop babbling]

1090
00:58:18,369 --> 00:58:20,205
-[phone buzzing]
-[Walt chuckles]

1091
00:58:23,458 --> 00:58:24,876
Quincey?

1092
00:58:24,959 --> 00:58:25,960
What's wrong?

1093
00:58:28,421 --> 00:58:30,548
Oh-- slow-- What's wrong?

1094
00:58:31,674 --> 00:58:33,843
Okay, okay. L-- No, no. Oh.

1095
00:58:33,927 --> 00:58:35,428
-We gotta go.
-What happened?

1096
00:58:35,512 --> 00:58:37,388
-We gotta go get Quincey.
-What's wrong?

1097
00:58:37,472 --> 00:58:38,640
Ketta, what's wrong?

1098
00:58:38,723 --> 00:58:41,726
[♪ tense, somber music playing]

1099
00:59:16,844 --> 00:59:19,847
[♪ tense, somber music
continues playing]

1100
00:59:42,537 --> 00:59:43,538
Yeah!

1101
00:59:55,508 --> 00:59:56,509
Lulu.

1102
00:59:58,595 --> 00:59:59,846
I'm gonna miss you, okay?

1103
01:00:00,179 --> 01:00:01,180
[kiss smacks]

1104
01:00:08,313 --> 01:00:10,773
[car door opens and closes]

1105
01:00:18,156 --> 01:00:20,867
[car door opens and closes]

1106
01:00:22,160 --> 01:00:24,162
[car starting]

1107
01:00:26,748 --> 01:00:28,750
[car driving away]

1108
01:00:49,270 --> 01:00:52,065
[chuckles] You just gonna push
that food around on your plate, Q,

1109
01:00:52,148 --> 01:00:53,232
or you gonna eat it?

1110
01:00:57,904 --> 01:00:59,614
Hey, you know the fellas
miss you, man.

1111
01:01:01,824 --> 01:01:04,243
Hey, if you lock back in,
I think we can--

1112
01:01:04,327 --> 01:01:05,995
we gonna have
a real shot at this thing.

1113
01:01:07,246 --> 01:01:08,706
I ain't fighting no more.

1114
01:01:10,249 --> 01:01:13,378
Could care less about it,
you, or anybody.

1115
01:01:14,337 --> 01:01:17,507
Boxing's still supposed to be
important to me right now, Walt?

1116
01:01:22,804 --> 01:01:25,390
Since when you stopped
calling me Coach?

1117
01:01:25,473 --> 01:01:26,933
Q, when-- when that happen?

1118
01:01:29,644 --> 01:01:33,523
[sighs] My mom just died.

1119
01:01:34,732 --> 01:01:37,235
So, right now, I could give
zero fucks about your pep talk.

1120
01:01:37,318 --> 01:01:38,319
[utensil hitting plate]

1121
01:01:38,403 --> 01:01:39,987
-Watch your mouth, man.
-[Ketta] Okay.

1122
01:01:40,655 --> 01:01:42,198
Okay. Everybody.

1123
01:01:43,449 --> 01:01:45,576
Quincey. Quincey.

1124
01:01:47,078 --> 01:01:49,288
You know your mama
was more to me than just a friend.

1125
01:01:50,581 --> 01:01:51,666
She was my sister.

1126
01:01:53,209 --> 01:01:55,503
So, that means I got you forever.

1127
01:01:56,838 --> 01:01:58,005
Okay?

1128
01:01:58,881 --> 01:02:00,466
-[Quincey sighs]
-[Ketta] We got you forever.

1129
01:02:02,635 --> 01:02:05,012
[Walt] Hey, man, listen.
If you scared, say you scared.

1130
01:02:05,096 --> 01:02:06,556
Walt.

1131
01:02:07,640 --> 01:02:08,641
Is that what it is?

1132
01:02:09,600 --> 01:02:11,561
If you scared, say you scared.

1133
01:02:16,733 --> 01:02:17,734
[chair scraping]

1134
01:02:17,817 --> 01:02:18,818
[feet stomping]

1135
01:02:20,319 --> 01:02:22,572
[door opens]

1136
01:02:22,655 --> 01:02:24,699
[door slamming shut]

1137
01:02:24,782 --> 01:02:26,242
What are you doing?

1138
01:02:26,325 --> 01:02:28,035
-What?
-What-- That's not it, man.

1139
01:02:29,036 --> 01:02:31,914
It's our job to make sure
that boy's dreams don't ever die.

1140
01:02:31,998 --> 01:02:34,500
All this, what, tough talk
or whatever?

1141
01:02:34,584 --> 01:02:36,961
That ain't it. It's not.

1142
01:02:40,798 --> 01:02:42,967
[door creaking open]

1143
01:02:43,926 --> 01:02:44,927
[door slams shut]

1144
01:02:53,978 --> 01:02:54,937
[fork clatters]

1145
01:02:57,106 --> 01:02:59,150
[scale rattling]

1146
01:03:05,573 --> 01:03:06,574
107?

1147
01:03:07,700 --> 01:03:08,993
Man, what you been eating?

1148
01:03:11,078 --> 01:03:12,663
[Slim]
Oh, this is bad, P.

1149
01:03:13,664 --> 01:03:15,208
You gotta fight your battles
outside the ring

1150
01:03:15,291 --> 01:03:16,542
just as much as in.

1151
01:03:16,626 --> 01:03:18,878
Okay, sacrifice, commitment, dedication.

1152
01:03:18,961 --> 01:03:20,630
We talked about this, man.

1153
01:03:20,713 --> 01:03:22,465
Come on.
Them words don't ring a bell to you?

1154
01:03:22,548 --> 01:03:25,259
Coach, I swear I've been eating clean.

1155
01:03:26,427 --> 01:03:28,054
Hop back on the scale, man.

1156
01:03:29,096 --> 01:03:31,098
[scale rattling]

1157
01:03:36,020 --> 01:03:37,730
-[Slim scoffs]
-[Walt] 107.

1158
01:03:38,481 --> 01:03:40,358
[Slim] You thinking what I'm thinking?

1159
01:03:40,441 --> 01:03:41,442
[Walt] Mm-hmm.

1160
01:03:41,692 --> 01:03:42,985
[Slim] [softly] Tell him.

1161
01:03:43,903 --> 01:03:45,613
[Walt exhales slowly]

1162
01:03:47,448 --> 01:03:49,867
You know this mean that you could
face off against Quincey.

1163
01:03:51,035 --> 01:03:52,203
If you both advance.

1164
01:03:54,205 --> 01:03:55,665
He's more disciplined
than you, Peanut.

1165
01:03:55,748 --> 01:03:58,042
He ain't never had
no trouble on the scale.

1166
01:03:58,125 --> 01:03:59,252
[Peanut] It don't even matter.

1167
01:03:59,335 --> 01:04:01,462
He ain't coming back.

1168
01:04:01,546 --> 01:04:03,506
You pick your head up.

1169
01:04:03,589 --> 01:04:04,715
Quincey or no Quincey.

1170
01:04:06,008 --> 01:04:08,219
We put you in that ring, you win it.

1171
01:04:10,179 --> 01:04:12,265
-You hear me?
-Yes, Coach.

1172
01:04:13,391 --> 01:04:15,184
[knocking at door]

1173
01:04:15,268 --> 01:04:16,394
[Walt] Can I get a minute?

1174
01:04:18,145 --> 01:04:19,897
I come in peace.

1175
01:04:26,320 --> 01:04:27,864
Q, I'm sorry about your mom.

1176
01:04:35,705 --> 01:04:38,165
You know, it look like you and, um,

1177
01:04:38,249 --> 01:04:40,626
you and Peanut might have to face off
against each other.

1178
01:04:42,420 --> 01:04:44,046
What, you just gonna give it to him?

1179
01:04:45,423 --> 01:04:47,383
I ain't never known you
to be no quitter.

1180
01:04:59,520 --> 01:05:00,605
Go ahead.

1181
01:05:02,899 --> 01:05:04,025
Go ahead.

1182
01:05:05,693 --> 01:05:07,737
-Go ahead, I know you wanna.
-[Quincey grunting angrily]

1183
01:05:08,905 --> 01:05:10,406
Go ahead. That's all you got?

1184
01:05:10,489 --> 01:05:12,617
-[Quincey grunting angrily]
-Come on! Come on.

1185
01:05:12,700 --> 01:05:14,452
-[Quincey grunts angrily]
-Aw, come on, man.

1186
01:05:14,535 --> 01:05:16,537
That's not all you got.
You can do better than that.

1187
01:05:16,621 --> 01:05:19,123
-Come on! Come on!
-[Quincey whimpers]

1188
01:05:22,043 --> 01:05:24,045
[Quincey sobbing]

1189
01:05:29,550 --> 01:05:31,052
It's gonna be alright.

1190
01:05:36,015 --> 01:05:37,099
I'm sorry.

1191
01:05:42,188 --> 01:05:44,190
[Peanut exhaling sharply]

1192
01:05:44,857 --> 01:05:46,692
[Peanut's dad] Hey.

1193
01:05:46,776 --> 01:05:48,069
Big guy.

1194
01:05:48,152 --> 01:05:49,862
Holla at your old man,
would you, baby?

1195
01:05:52,198 --> 01:05:53,199
Hey, Dad.

1196
01:05:54,283 --> 01:05:56,827
I hear you learning that
sweet science, ain't you?

1197
01:05:56,911 --> 01:05:59,789
Yeah. Think I'm getting
pretty good at it.

1198
01:05:59,872 --> 01:06:00,998
I love hearing that.

1199
01:06:01,916 --> 01:06:02,917
My son.

1200
01:06:04,961 --> 01:06:08,005
That gym will teach you a lot
I never got the opportunity to, Peanut.

1201
01:06:08,881 --> 01:06:10,508
I mean, you should come
see me fight then.

1202
01:06:10,591 --> 01:06:11,926
[Peanut's dad] I really want to, man.

1203
01:06:12,009 --> 01:06:14,428
Just started this new gig,
they won't give me the time off, you know?

1204
01:06:16,681 --> 01:06:19,725
It's okay.
You can come to the next one.

1205
01:06:23,187 --> 01:06:25,523
You got a couple dollars
you can let your old man borrow?

1206
01:06:30,319 --> 01:06:31,570
Nah.

1207
01:06:31,654 --> 01:06:33,197
Buy everything with my phone.

1208
01:06:34,407 --> 01:06:35,783
True.

1209
01:06:35,866 --> 01:06:37,284
True, true, true, true.

1210
01:06:37,368 --> 01:06:38,369
True.

1211
01:06:44,250 --> 01:06:45,960
You know, I ain't never won anything, man.

1212
01:06:47,253 --> 01:06:48,754
No trophies.

1213
01:06:48,838 --> 01:06:50,131
No nothing, just...

1214
01:06:51,674 --> 01:06:53,467
Getting my clothing line
off the ground.

1215
01:06:54,468 --> 01:06:55,636
That's my big win.

1216
01:06:56,637 --> 01:06:58,222
Huh, what you say, Peanut?

1217
01:07:04,353 --> 01:07:06,063
How come you never married Mom?

1218
01:07:19,869 --> 01:07:22,788
Okay, Peanut, you know,
you should get back at it.

1219
01:07:24,832 --> 01:07:26,834
[train horn blaring in distance]

1220
01:07:35,092 --> 01:07:38,095
[♪ intense music playing]

1221
01:07:42,641 --> 01:07:43,642
